tei:div.p:
“With their knowledge of insight, bodhisattvas engage in the discernment of meaning and doctrine;
                                                yet they also engage in the discernment of expression and eloquence, through their knowledge of
                                                skillful means.

The monks replied, “There is no guidance aimed at the abiding nature, yet there is also no
                                                absence of such guidance; it is known, just as it is. There is neither producing nor obstructing it;
                                                things are known to be sameness.”
